{
  "texts": [
    "They compared these students' performance with other EFL students at similar English writing levels and found that after a 12-week experiment, the average International English Language Testing System (IELTS) writing score of students assisted by ChatGPT increased by about one-third compared to those assisted by human experts, with scores of 59.12 and 45.18 respectively [11].",
    "Boudouaia, Mouas, and Kouider's research demonstrated a similar result.",
    "They found that students who revised their papers based on ChatGPT's suggestions performed better in the post-test than those who did not and showed significant improvement compared to their pre-test scores [12].",
    "However, Algaraady and Mahyoob discovered ChatGPT's shortages in recognizing writing errors.",
    "They found that ChatGPT can efficiently catch surface-level mistakes like grammar, spelling, and punctuation errors."
  ]
}